    - params (np.ndarray): Trainable coefficients used by the equation skeleton.
    """
    """Improved version of `equation_v1`.

    Physical motivation:
    - Linear restoring force ~ x0 (usually negative coefficient)
    - Linear damping ~ x1 (usually negative coefficient)
    - Cubic stiffness nonlinearity ~ x0^3 (Duffing term)
    - Nonlinear damping ~ x1^3 or other powers
    - Pendulum-like nonlinearity ~ sin(x0)
