    - Retains all previous polynomial and trig terms for position and velocity

    Physical motivation:
    - Quartic stiffness/damping nonlinearities to capture stronger anharmonic effects
    - Mixed trig-polynomial terms model modulation of damping/restoring forces by periodic potentials
    - Maintains linear, quadratic, cubic terms for baseline nonlinear oscillator behavior

    Parameters (params[0] to params[11]):
        0: constant offset
        1: linear position term coefficient (~ -omega^2)
        2: linear velocity term coefficient (~ -c)
